<div id="about">
  <div id="index-banner" class="parallax-container">
    <div class="section no-pad-bot">
      <div class="container">
        <br><br>
        <h1 class="header center">About Us</h1>
        <br><br>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="parallax">
      <%= image_tag "cmu-banner-7.jpg" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="section">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col s12 center">
          <h3><i class="mdi-content-send brown-text"></i></h3>
          <h4 class="header secondary-color">Professional Development Services</h4>
          <p class="center-align banner-text">Professional Development Services Our Focus is You. Simply stated, the mission of Professional Development Services is to support you in your role at Carnegie Mellon University. We believe our success is reflected in your success as you utilize the programs, services, and resources we offer. Our commitment is to provide valuable learning experiences that empower you to maximize your performance and achieve your full potential. By framing professional development in a comprehensive manner, we encourage you to access and use the information and activities most relevant to your position and aspirations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="section">

      <ul id="tabs-swipe-demo" class="tabs tabs-fixed-width">
        <li class="tab col s3"><a class="active" href="#paradigms">Paradigms</a></li>
        <li class="tab col s3"><a href="#competencies">Competencies</a></li>
        <li class="tab col s3"><a href="#companion-champion">Companion to Champion</a></li>
      </ul>


      <div id="paradigms" class="col s12">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 center">
            <h3><i class="mdi-content-send brown-text"></i></h3>
            <h4 class="header secondary-color">Our Professional Development Paradigm</h4>
            <p class="center-align banner-text">We get you. We get CMU. We understand the degree of excellence that is expected of you. We understand your time is valuable and your work is important. We recognize you as an adult learner and value the talents, abilities, and experiences you possess. We encourage you to think beyond traditional training approaches and urge you to take full advantage of the opportunities you have to build your skills and abilities every day.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">find_in_page</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Build Understanding</h5>
              <p class="light center">One of the easiest and most convenient ways to expand your knowledge is by reading. Stay up-to-date on new trends and innovations in your field as a great way to stay motivated.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">assessment</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Do Something</h5>
              <p class="light center">Identify a particular skill or ability and create a strategy on how you will implement it into your work. Build time into your schedule to practice the skill.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">show_chart</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Learn More</h5>
              <p class="light center">Gaining new skills, ideas and knowledge plays an important role in job satisfaction and career development. Attend a workshop to learn best practices and the foundational theory on a particular topic. Engage with other colleagues to allow for the vital exchange of ideas and experiences. Take the opportunity to practice the concepts delivered in the session and discuss the ways in which they apply to your work allows you to determine their relevance and usefulness to you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">find_in_page</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Think About It</h5>
              <p class="light center">Reflection is a great tool to use for professional development. Taking the time to think about your work, challenges and progress is extremely beneficial.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">assessment</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Engage With Others</h5>
              <p class="light center">Exchange thoughts, offer support and share best practices to grow in your own skills by learning from others and their experiences.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">show_chart</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Get Connected</h5>
              <p class="light center">Utilizing technology to enhance your learning is convenient and flexible. You can augment instructor-led workshops, complete on-demand webinars or courses and get timely answers to your questions.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>


      <div id="competencies" class="col s12">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 center">
            <h3><i class="mdi-content-send brown-text"></i></h3>
            <h4 class="header secondary-color">Building Competence</h4>
            <p class="center-align banner-text">A competency is made up of demonstrable performance or behaviors that are grounded in content and context. There are three types of skills within each competence, and each type is demonstrated by specific behavioral indicators.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">find_in_page</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Cognitive Skills</h5>
              <p class="light center">Cognitive Skills include your ability to think critically and analyze, see the significance of observations and events, anticipate future events, problem solve, and select the best course of action.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">assessment</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Psychomotor Skills</h5>
              <p class="light center">Psychomotor Skills include your ability to perform physical tasks, such as using muscle memory to complete routine tasks, and your ability to develop skills through on the job training.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col s12 m4">
            <div class="icon-block">
              <h2 class="center brown-text"><i class="material-icons">show_chart</i></h2>
              <h5 class="center secondary-color">Interpersonal Skills</h5>
              <p class="light center">Interpersonal Skills include your ability to work and interact with others, collaborate, and resolve conflict.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
          <ul class="collection with-header center">
            <li class="collection-header"><h4 class="secondary-color">Our Foundational Competencies</h4></li>
            <li class="collection-item">Communication</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Creativity and Innovation</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Decision Making</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Intercultural Awareness</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Managing Conflict</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Priority Management</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Problem Solving</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Strategic Visioning</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Utilizing Technology</li>
            <li class="collection-item">Working with Others</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div id="companion-champion" class="col s12">  
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col s12 center">
            <h3><i class="mdi-content-send brown-text"></i></h3>
            <h4 class="header secondary-color">Companion to Champion Model</h4>
            <p class="center-align banner-text">We developed a competency model to meet your specific learning needs based on what we know about Carnegie Mellon University. Each level of mastery corresponds with the expected, observable behavioral indicators for a particular competence area. It is important to note that your level of mastery does not equate to your position or place on an organizational chart. You develop your skills and abilities in a variety of ways and often beyond your role at CMU. We hope to assist you in recognizing your level of mastery and provide suggestions on how to build upon your abilities.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row center">
          <a class="waves-effect waves-light btn" href="#companion">Companion</a>
          <div id="companion" class="modal">
            <div class="modal-content">
              <h4>Companion</h4>
              <p>As a Companion, you are beginning your journey to develop this competency through learning new skills and approaches. You benefit when instruction and support is provided.</p>
              <p>Education, training, coaching and practice</p>
              <p>Testing and observations</p>
            </div>
            <button class="modal-action modal-close btn-flat" >X</button>
          </div>

          <a class="waves-effect waves-light btn" href="#contributer">Contributer</a>
          <div id="contributer" class="modal">
            <div class="modal-content">
              <h4>Contributer</h4>
              <p>As a Contributor, you are someone who has developed a strong foundation of skills within this competency, but you want to increase your abilities and achieve consistent application.</p>
              <p>Access to knowledge and performance resources, coaching and practice</p>
              <p>Organizational contributions</p>
            </div>
            <button class="modal-action modal-close btn-flat">X</button>
          </div>

          <a class="waves-effect waves-light btn" href="#champion">Champion</a>
          <div id="champion" class="modal">
            <div class="modal-content">
              <h4>Champion</h4>
              <p>As a Champion, you are someone who has a practiced understanding of this competency. You strive to integrate the strategies and skills you have developed and apply these skills to the challenges and opportunities you face. You are able to support others in the development of this competency.</p>
              <p>Collaboration and problem-solving</p>
              <p>Innovation</p>
            </div>
            <button class="modal-action modal-close btn-flat">X</button>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="section">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col s12 center">
          <h3><i class="mdi-content-send brown-text"></i></h3>
          <h4 class="header secondary-color">Your Professional Development Plan</h4>
          <p class="center-align banner-text">Once you complete a competency assessment, save the link to your assessment report and thesuggested strategies to build competence in a given area. The suggestions are framed using our professional development paradigm and the related competency indicators. From there, you can utilize your plan to set professional development goals, schedule workshops and activities, and share your plan with your supervisor or co-worker.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>